@startuml 12-watchlist-rest-sequence
title Watchlists / REST Command — End-to-End Sequence

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam SequenceArrowColor #1f4e79
skinparam SequenceLifeLineBorderColor #1f4e79
skinparam ParticipantBorderColor #1f4e79
skinparam ParticipantBackgroundColor #e7eef7
skinparam NoteBorderColor #b3c4d9
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor #fff8e1

actor "REST Client\n(Postman / curl)" as client
participant "WatchlistRestController\n[driving adapter]" as ctrl
participant "WatchlistUseCase\n(application port in)" as usecase
participant "WatchlistService\n(watchlists)\nimplements UseCase" as svc
participant "WatchlistPort\n(application port out)" as portOut
participant "JpaWatchlistAdapter\n[driven adapter]" as jpa
database  "MySQL" as db

client -> ctrl : POST /api/watchlists/{id}/alerts\n{ ticker, thresholdPrice }
activate ctrl
ctrl -> ctrl : map DTO -> domain VOs\n(Ticker, Money)

ctrl -> usecase : addAlertEntry(id, ticker, threshold)
note right of ctrl
  Driving adapter rule
  (same as the @Scheduled adapter in 07):
  the controller depends on the
  inbound port, not on the service.
  REST, scheduler and tests all enter
  through the same port.
end note
activate usecase

usecase -> svc : addAlertEntry(...)
activate svc
svc -> portOut : getWatchlistById(id)
portOut -> jpa : findById(id)
jpa -> db : SELECT ...
db --> jpa : row(s)
jpa --> portOut : Optional<Watchlist>
portOut --> svc : Optional<Watchlist>

svc -> svc : watchlist.addAlert(ticker, threshold)
note right of svc
  All invariant checks live in
  the aggregate (domain layer):
  uniqueness of (ticker, threshold),
  active-state guard, etc.
end note

svc -> portOut : saveWatchlist(watchlist)
portOut -> jpa : save(entity)
jpa -> db : UPDATE / INSERT
db --> jpa : ok
jpa --> portOut : ok
portOut --> svc : ok

svc --> usecase : updated Watchlist
deactivate svc
usecase --> ctrl : updated Watchlist
deactivate usecase

ctrl -> ctrl : WatchlistResponseDTO.from(watchlist)
ctrl --> client : 200 OK\nWatchlistResponseDTO
deactivate ctrl

note over ctrl, jpa
  Symmetry with diagram 07:
  - Diagram 07: Scheduler (driving adapter) -> MarketSentinelUseCase (port-in) -> service.
  - Diagram 12: Controller (driving adapter) -> WatchlistUseCase    (port-in) -> service.
  Replace the controller by another driving adapter (a Telegram bot, a CLI,
  another @Scheduled job, an integration test) and nothing changes
  inside the hexagon -- that is the whole point of ports & adapters.
end note

note over portOut, jpa
  Today there is one inbound port
  (WatchlistUseCase, command side)
  and one outbound port
  (WatchlistPort, CRUD).
  A read-side port (WatchlistQueryPort)
  exists for the sentinel's projections.
  If a query API is added later we can
  split the inbound port into
  WatchlistCommandUseCase /
  WatchlistQueryUseCase without
  touching the controller's contract.
end note

@enduml
